The paper presents a machine learning model that incorporates domain knowledge from physics, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category since the paper is primarily focused on developing a machine learning model. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely since the paper discusses using domain knowledge to improve the model's performance. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category since the paper discusses using the model to learn system dynamics. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category since the paper uses variational inference to obtain a sparse approximation. Finally, cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a possible category since the paper discusses using the model to model complex physical systems.
